    "read": "Today has an expansion tone, but it is not clean or effortless. You may notice more doors cracking open through conversations, documents, introductions, or quiet signs that your work is starting to travel further than your current title or setup. The useful move is to build leverage without rushing to lock everything in. Ask better questions, update the paper trail, clarify expectations, and keep relationships warm, especially with people who can later support a more formal step. The tension is that your foundations still feel loaded: home, money, family logistics, repairs, debt, shared resources, or emotional bandwidth may all demand more maturity than you would prefer. This is a stretch for your nervous system because the opportunity signal is real, but the background pressure is also real. Do not confuse movement with readiness. Work benefits from precise communication today. Say what you mean, but avoid forcing agreement before the structure is ready. Money decisions should be practical, not symbolic. Relationships may bring useful clarity, but not necessarily comfort. Fewer, cleaner moves beat big declarations. Open the door now; make it weight-bearing later."
